  "text": "Some surgical procedures require good muscle relaxation. The lungs are ventilated according to the principles of the lung protective strategy using positive end-expiratory pressure (PEEP). Low flow anaesthesia (LFA) techniques are Fear of mask also acceptable, but not in children < 2 years of age or with body weight < 20 kg due to the risk of hypoxia [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . Alternatively, total intravenous anaesthesia (TIVA) can be performed, most commonly with propofol; however, the depth of anaesthesia should be monitored to avoid awareness during surgery. In children with hemodynamic instability, TIVA with ketamine can be used.",
